Brian's Sweet Pizza Sauce

Inspired By: https://www.kingarthurbaking.com/recipes/buttermilk-pancakes-recipe

Wet Ingredients:

1 cup Buttermilk

Dry Ingredients:

1 cups (241g) King Arthur Unbleached All-Purpose Flour
3 tablespoons malted milk powder
1/2 teaspoon baking powder
1/2 teaspoon baking soda
1/4 teaspoon salt
1/2 large egg
1 cups (454g) buttermilk
1 tablespoons (28g) melted butter or 2 tablespoons (25g) vegetable oil
3/4 teaspoons vanilla extract, optional

Process:

Heat cast iron Comal, Pan, or Griddle to between 350-375F
If you dont have Sourmilk, make it 10 minutes before you begin
Add all remaining ingredients and simmer 30-60 minutes, uncovered.

Tips:

To make substitute buttermilk, combine one tablespoon of Vinegar or Lemon juice with one per cup of milk and let stand for 10 minutes.
